<item>
            <title>[PIG-2161] TOTUPLE should use no-copy tuple creation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2161</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TOTUPLE udf gets an input tuple, creates a new list, puts every field from the tuple into the list, and creates a new tuple by calling TupleFactory.newTuple(List&amp;lt;Object&amp;gt;) method &amp;#8211; which in turn allocates &lt;b&gt;another&lt;/b&gt; list and copies everything in there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simply returning the input tuple should be sufficient &amp;#8211; Pig already did the work of putting the arguments into a tuple.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
